org.openhubframework.openhub.api.asynch.finalmessage

Interface FinalMessageProcessor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.springframework.core.Ordered
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFinalMessageProcessor, DeleteFinalMessageProcessor
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface FinalMessageProcessor
extends org.springframework.core.Ordered
    Contract for final messages processor. Messages that are no-longer considered relevant for openhub async workflow are expected to be processed by this processor. There can be multiple processors, that are invoked in order defined in getOrder method. All processor are expected to be executed in transaction, if any should throw an exception, transaction will be rolled back.
    Since:
    2.1
    Author:
    Karel Kovarik
